President Muhammadu Buhari and the Katsina State Governor, Aminu Masari, are currently meeting at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. This was made known by Buhari’s Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu on twitter. According to the Presidential Spokesman, the Katsina governor was summoned by the President to an urgent meeting on the security situation in the State. President @MBuhari summons Katsina State Governor, Aminu Bello Masari to an urgent meeting on the security situation in the state. — Garba Shehu (@GarShehu) May 22, 2019  The Governor went into the meeting with the President at 9:30 pm, and the discussion between them is still ongoing at this hour. — Garba Shehu (@GarShehu) May 22, 2019  Details shortly…